  "prompt": "What makeup to wear for red dress?",
  "response": "A red dress is a statement piece, so you want your makeup to complement it without overpowering it. Here's a breakdown of makeup looks that work well with a red dress, categorized by the impact you want to create:\n\n**1. Classic & Timeless:**\n\n*   **Skin:** Flawless, even-toned complexion. Use a foundation that matches your skin tone perfectly.  A satin or semi-matte finish is elegant. Conceal any blemishes or dark circles.\n*   **Cheeks:**  Soft blush in a peachy-pink or rose shade. Apply to the apples of your cheeks and blend upwards. Avoid anything too orange or coral, as it can clash with the red dress.\n*   **Eyes:**\n    *   **Option 1: Defined Eyes:** A classic black winged liner with a touch of neutral eyeshadow (taupe, light brown) on the lid.  A light shimmery shade in the inner corner will brighten the eyes.  Mascara is a must!\n    *   **Option 2: Soft Smoky Eye:** A neutral smoky eye using shades of brown, bronze, or grey. Blend well for a diffused look.  Again, mascara is crucial.\n*   **Lips:** A classic red lip is always a winner! Choose a shade that complements your skin tone and the shade of red in your dress. Consider a matte or satin finish for longevity.  Alternatively, a nude or berry lip can also work well if you want to keep the focus on the dress.\n*   **Brows:** Well-groomed brows are essential. Fill them in with a brow pencil or powder to frame your face.\n\n**2. Modern & Chic:**\n\n*   **Skin:** Dewy, healthy-looking skin. Use a hydrating foundation or tinted moisturizer.  Highlight your cheekbones, brow bone, and cupid's bow with a subtle highlighter.\n*   **Cheeks:**  Cream blush in a berry or rose shade for a natural flush.\n*   **Eyes:**\n    *   **Option 1:  Graphic Liner:** A bold graphic eyeliner look.  Think a sharp wing, a floating liner, or a geometric shape.  Keep the eyeshadow minimal.\n    *   **Option 2:  Monochromatic Eyes:**  Use a single eyeshadow shade in a neutral or warm tone (bronze, copper, gold) all over the lid.  Blend well.\n*   **Lips:** A nude lip with a glossy finish.  You can also try a berry-stained lip for a more modern take.\n*   **Brows:**  Defined but natural-looking brows.  Use a brow gel to keep them in place.\n\n**3. Bold & Dramatic:**\n\n*   **Skin:** Matte, flawless complexion. Use a full-coverage foundation and set with powder.  Contour your cheekbones and jawline for definition.\n*   **Cheeks:**  Contoured cheeks with a pop of blush in a berry or plum shade.\n*   **Eyes:**\n    *   **Option 1:  Dramatic Smoky Eye:** A smoky eye in shades of black, grey, or deep purple.  Use a gel liner on the waterline for extra intensity.\n    *   **Option 2:  Cut Crease:**  A defined cut crease with a contrasting eyeshadow color.\n*   **Lips:** A deep red, burgundy, or plum lipstick.  A matte finish will last longer.\n*   **Brows:**  Bold, defined brows.\n\n**Key Considerations:**\n\n*   **Undertones:** Match your makeup undertones to your skin's undertones (warm, cool, neutral).  This will help you choose colors that flatter your complexion.\n*   **Dress Shade:** The specific shade of red in your dress will influence your makeup choices.  A brighter red can handle bolder makeup, while a deeper red may require a more subtle approach.\n*   **Occasion:**  Consider the occasion. A formal event calls for more polished makeup, while a casual outing allows for a more relaxed look.\n*   **Personal Style:**  Ultimately, your makeup should reflect your personal style.  Don't be afraid to experiment and find what works best for you!\n\n**Tips for Choosing the Right Red Lipstick:**\n\n*   **Cool Undertones:** Look for reds with blue or purple undertones (e.g., cherry red, raspberry red).\n*   **Warm Undertones:** Look for reds with orange or yellow undertones (e.g., brick red, tomato red).\n*   **Neutral Undertones:** You can wear most reds!\n\n**General Advice:**\n\n*   **Less is More:** When in doubt, err on the side of less makeup. A red dress is already a statement, so you don't want to look overdone.\n*   **Balance:** If you're going for a bold lip, keep the eyes relatively simple. If you're doing a dramatic eye look, opt for a more neutral lip.\n*   **Prime:** Use a good primer before applying your foundation and eyeshadow to help your makeup last longer.\n*   **Set:** Set your makeup with a setting spray to prevent it from smudging or fading.\n*   **Practice:** Practice your makeup look before the event to ensure you're happy with the results.\n\nNo matter what look you choose, remember to feel confident and beautiful in your red dress!\n",
